{"id":"coal-petroleum-8","label":"Coal and Petroleum","lockAfter":2,"list":[{"id":"mcq","label":"Choose the correct answer","type":"mcq","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Questions"},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Minerals are","options":"exhaustible natural resources, not natural resources, inexhaustible natural resources, all of these"},{"qText":"Petroleum is mainly a mixture of which one of the following class?","options":"Hydrocarbons, Carbohydrates, Carbogens, Alcohols"},{"qText":"Which one is not a coal product?","options":"Lime, Coal tar, Coal gas"},{"qText":"Which one of the following is a petrochemical?","options":"Ammonia, Paraffin wax, Coke, Acetone"},{"qText":"Conversion of dead vegetation into coal is called","options":"carbonisation, distillation, coal gas, natural gas"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"What is the full form of LPG?","options":"Liquefied Petroleum Gas, Light Petroleum Gas, Long Pipe of Gas, Long Petroleum Gas"},{"qText":" A natural gas stored under high pressure in compressed form is called","options":"CNG, LPG, KLG, PNP"},{"qText":"Name the petroleum product used for surfacing of road","options":"Bitumen, Peat, Lignite, Anthracite"},{"qText":"Products obtained by the process of destructive distillation are","options":"coke, coal-tar, coal gas\n                petrol, diesel, kerosene\n                paraffin wax, bitumen\n                compressed natural gas"},{"qText":"The mining of oil under sea is termed as","options":"shore mining, distillation, carbonisation, destructive distillation"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Main constituent of LPG is","options":"butane and propane, methane, butane, propane"},{"qText":"Least polluting fuel for vehicles is","options":"CNG, coke, kerosene, diesel"},{"qText":"Petroleum is found under the","options":"sedimentary rocks, water, sand, coke"},{"qText":"Which of the following is a renewable source of energy?","options":"Water, Natural gas, Petroleum, Coal"},{"qText":"Which of the following is a non-renewable source of energy?","options":"Coal, Sun, Water, Soil"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Fossil fuels are","options":"natural gas, coal, petroleum, * all of the these"},{"qText":"Naphthalene balls are used as ","options":"moth repellant, bee repellant, mosquito repellant, snake repellant"},{"qText":"The process of conversion of wood into coal is called","options":"Carbonization, Carboniferous, Catagenesis"},{"qText":"Petroleum is also known as","options":"black gold, liquid gold, black diamond, liquid diamond"},{"qText":"The brown variety of coal is ","options":"lignite, bituminous, peat, anthracite"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"The major constituent of natural gas is","options":"methane, butane, ethane, hydrogen"},{"qText":"The product obtained by destructive distillation of coal is","options":"coal gas, coal tar, coke, * all of these"},{"qText":"Which is the best type of coal?","options":"Anthracite, Peat, Lignite, Bituminous"},{"qText":"Petroleum is separated by using the difference in","options":"boiling points, melting points, freezing points, ignition temperatures"}]}]}]}